---
import Section from '../../../components/core/layout/Section.astro';
import ContentLayout from '../../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';

// image imports
import fatalis from '../../../assets/world/builds/endgame/fatalis.png';
import alatreonFire from '../../../assets/world/builds/endgame/alatreon_fire.png';
import alatreonIce from '../../../assets/world/builds/endgame/alatreon_ice.png';
import BuildCard from '../../../components/builds/BuildCard.astro';
import Tabs from '../../../components/core/tabs/Tabs.astro';
---

<ContentLayout>
  <Section>
    <p>
      Congratulations on conquering Fatalis, the ultimate challenge of Monster Hunter World! Now
      that you've defeated the legendary Black Dragon, it's time to harness its power by crafting
      the game's strongest equipment. This section showcases the definitive endgame builds for
      lance.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="The Fatalis Empire" emoji="ðŸ‰">
    <p>
      The Fatalis Lance stands uncontested as the premier weapon for lance users. Its exceptional
      raw damage overcomes the negative affinity penalty through the equally powerful Fatalis armor
      set. This combination represents the pinnacle of lance builds, optimal for virtually every
      monster in the game with the possible exception of Alatreon.
    </p>

    <p>
      Fatalis armor's abundance of decoration slots allows for unprecedented build flexibility. The
      template below balances peak damage output with practical defensive skills, creating a
      comfortable yet powerful endgame experience.
    </p>

    <BuildCard
      build={{
        title: 'Black Dragon Sovereign',
        description: [
          'The Fatalis Lance boasts unmatched raw damage at the cost of negative affinity. We mitigate this through multiple affinity-boosting skills to reach the 100% critical hit cap for consistent damage.',
          'Four pieces of Fatalis armor provide two game-changing set bonuses: Transcendence grants maximum health and stamina caps plus True Razor Sharp for effortless sharpness management, while Inheritance unlocks all skill secrets without requiring specific armor combinations.',
          "We complement the Fatalis pieces with Arch-Tempered Velkhana legs for Peak Performance 3, adding substantial attack power that's easily maintained through our health augment. This combination delivers the perfect balance of offensive potential and practical comfort for all endgame content.",
        ],
        image: fatalis,
        imageAlt: 'Fatalis Armor and Lance',
        stats: {
          raw: 1027,
          sharpness: {
            hits: 60,
            type: 'purple',
          },
          affinity: {
            avg: 100,
            peak: 100,
          },
          element: {
            type: 'dragon',
            value: 19,
          },
        },
        augments: ['health', 'health', 'health', 'affinity', 'affinity', 'defense'],
        additionalNotes: {
          'Weapon Augments':
            'We get a health augment to help with chip damage and peak performance uptime. Then we also get an affinity augment so we can reach 100% affinity. And with the last augment slot we get the defense augment because the damage increase from the element augment is not noticeable.',
        },
      }}
    />
  </Section>

  <Section title="Anti Alatreon Sets" emoji="ðŸ²">
    <p>
      Alatreon presents a unique endgame challenge with its unusual hitzone values. Despite common
      assumptions, Alatreon actually features excellent raw hitzones while its elemental hitzones
      are less impressive, especially during Dragon active state.
    </p>

    <p>
      This creates an interesting optimization puzzle: the fastest kill times come from raw-focused
      weapons, but you must deal sufficient elemental damage to survive the Escaton Judgment. While
      experienced hunters might choose to run Fortify and simply accept the cart from Escaton, these
      specialized elemental builds offer a more consistent approach.
    </p>

    <p>
      The Safi'jiiva weapons provide ideal customization through their awakening system. By
      carefully balancing elemental and raw awakenings, we can meet the elemental threshold while
      maintaining strong raw damage. Any lance with 400+ displayed element should comfortably reach
      the topple threshold with aggressive play.
    </p>

    <Tabs
      labels={[
        { id: 'fire', display: 'fire' },
        { id: 'ice', display: 'ice' },
      ]}
    >
      <div id="fire">
        <BuildCard
          build={{
            title: 'Dawn Harbinger ðŸ”¥',
            description: [
              "The Safi'jiiva Fire Lance provides the perfect balance of raw damage and fire element when customized with appropriate awakenings. This makes it ideal for Alatreon's Ice active state.",
              'We intentionally overcap on affinity to maintain 100% critical hit rate without tenderizing - a significant quality-of-life improvement against Alatreon, where maintaining tenderized parts can be challenging due to his mobility and attack patterns.',
              "Fatalis armor's Transcendence bonus ensures our sharpness remains manageable throughout the fight, while Inheritance allows access to Agitator 7 without restrictive armor combinations. The set's abundant decoration slots accommodate all our core damage skills plus elemental attack and comfort options.",
              'The AT Velkhana greaves complete the build with Peak Performance 3, providing additional raw damage that synergizes perfectly with our health augment.',
            ],
            image: alatreonFire,
            imageAlt: 'Alatreon Fire Lance',
            stats: {
              raw: 804,
              sharpness: {
                hits: 60,
                type: 'purple',
              },
              affinity: {
                avg: 100,
                peak: 100,
              },
              element: {
                type: 'fire',
                value: 64,
              },
            },
            augments: ['health', 'health', 'health', 'affinity', 'affinity', 'element'],
            additionalNotes: {
              'Weapon Augments':
                'We get a health augment to help with chip damage and peak performance uptime. Then we also get an affinity augment so we can reach 100% affinity. And with the last augment slot we get the element augment to get the most out of our Safi Awakenings.',
              'Safi Awakenings':
                "For the safi awakenings we're gonna be using 3 element 5 awakenings, an attack 5 and an attack 6 augment.",
            },
          }}
        />
      </div>
      <div id="ice">
        <BuildCard
          build={{
            title: 'Frost Sovereign ðŸ§Š',
